caption: Amazing vibes and very amiable service. The menu was fresh and delightful. Will absolutely recommend this spot to friends. Fair rates and generous meals. Good job.
It was delicious. I had such a good time I didn’t even take pictures. That’s how much I was enjoying.
Great Brisket, wings and sticky rice.
Expensive and not good
The food is off the chain! Everything is good and the customer service is A1!
A fav location for delicious Korean food. This location is one of my favorites. The service was friendly and observant. It has a nice atmosphere. Mood here reminds me of Colorado Springs area.

The chicken was really good. I especially enjoyed the spicy ones. They’re really a gochujang flavor. But there was plenty of saucy goodness. And the servings of fries was huge. 💕 I was a happy child after this meal.
So delicious! I love Korean Food and was so thrilled to find that this place had Halal options! We will definitely be coming back!
The food was not great. The korean chicken and steak tacos were very greasy.
Delicious and casual Korean BBQ spot. Great value for a lot of food!
Authentic and good!!
Chicken wings are great, ribeye > brisket, big portions, everything was fresh, we'll be back soon!
Great BBQ!
Absolutely delicious food and excellent customer service. We only ate their halal options but the taste of everything was on point!
We had an amazing experience at this place. We liked the great atmosphere and the menu. The staff members are super friendly. I am content we ultimately decided to visit here.

My first time eating Korean Food, so I did not know what to expect. I got the chicken bowl with an egg and did not regret it! Very tasty. Only downside is the bowl doesn't have as much chicken as it does rice and veggies. Plus side, the food is halal.
The guy running SoJu is super nice, and the food is great!
Great food!

This place was decent. We got the kimchi dumplings and they were super tasty with the perfect amount of spice. I got the bulgogi bowl and it was just ok. Came with tons of rice and veggies but the smallest portion of bulgogi which was kinda disappointing.  I asked for spicy but it tasted like they didn't season with anything but soy sauce. No biggie, I just asked for some of their chili sauce and it tasted much better. My hubby got the tofu and spicy rice cake skewers and said they were delicious. So all in all this place was a good last minute choice.

Loved the fried chicken. When you get chicken wings from anywhere, usually the skin got the sauce and that's about it.but these wings got flavor all the way inside. Very well cooked and tasty. Loved the beef ribs with the sticky rice and the chili sweet sauce was to die for. All in all, it was a great experience and will definitely go back soon. Thanks for great food :)
We ordered the kimchi fries and bulgogi fries here through doordash, it was amazing! My boyfriend loved the bulgogi fries and the kimchi fries hit the spot for me! Will be ordering again!
Very rude place. I asked for a cup of water then the guy told me coldly "No, 50 cents." Then they said, "We're closed." Cheap and confusing. I wouldn't recommend bringing your date or children here.

I come to this marvelous  restaurant from time to time since I like the  special atmosphere that is part of this restaurant. The crew is extraordianrillyremarkably welcoming and experienced. The service is certainly efficient. Needless to say, the food you get is first-rate. I frequent often and I was always delighted. The price is reasobable. I recommend this place to to all.

1st time ordering and 1 Star is for the flimsy excuse given to me my the so - called manager when I called about my Korean fried chicken wing order had only 6 pieces for $10.99.  She said well sometimes its 6 and sometimes its 8 IF you order from the app. I told her that makes no sense because it's not posted on the website AND the price is still the same!  The amount of pieces should be the same regardless!  A lousy way to do business and I wouldn't be ordering  or referring anyone to this restaurant!

This place is the one I like best. I eat in plenty of restaurants but here I go the most. The crew is very welcoming and the cuisine they place on your table is so good. I am always happy to have a good meal in this restaurant. I recommend this place with pleasure.
Good portion sizes. I got the loaded fries and tacos! Everything was really yummy and tasted fresh.
Friendly and nice server. Also, food is tasty
Since I'm unable to travel to 서울 right now.  Soju BBQ bring s서울  to  me through UberEat.  I really enjoy the food from here.  감사합니다!!!
I love the vegetarian tacos!

Impeccable quality and service. Little difference between takeout and eating in. Owner and staff go above and beyond in their service. Highly recommend the bulgogi, ribs, pork, chicken, dumplings, kimchi fried rice, and loaded fries- plus you can’t forget about their awesome sides!
The meals and service were ahead of our expectations. We absolutely liked the atmosphere of this spot. Extraordinary spot to take my family out for dinner.
The best Korean food I've ever eaten. And I'm from LA. Also, the people who work here are super chill and friendly.

Really good Korean bbq. Great service once sat. My fiancé loved the tofu soup and the cheese corn is amazing. Of course all the meats are delicious,m. The reason is why I remove one star is that the manager/owner is kind of rude. Whenever I come in, it doesn't seem like he cares if I stay or not and I've walked away a few times because of this. But once sat down, the servers are cool.
Awesome food and hospitality!

I’ve been here several times and always leave impressed with the quality of the food. The best part is that it is *halal.* Great overall high-quality Korean restaurant with a fast-casual atmosphere and pricing.
The food is exquisite and the service is excellent. The atmosphere is casual and comfortable. It was nice to be able to BYOB.

We like a lot eating out. Last night we came to this fine restaurant which friends told us about. We had a beautiful experience there with high-qulity cooking and an efficient team and a great  cuisine. We put this place in our phone list  and we will certainly visit again soon. We deeply recommend.
The place is fantastic and roomy, the food was delicious and the rates were very inexpensive. quickly, productive service and very amiable waiters. Will definitely recommend this place.
The place offers a great range of fresh food. I love eating here. Employees are always very friendly, prices are convenient and the spot is always clean.
I felt this place was overpriced and the portion sizes very small, left hungry after spending $20+.  The taste and flavor was also average.
Excellent and delightful food, I liked the ambience this spot has, and the employees were super nice. Will surely visit here when I’m around.
Place is great for lunch and serves great specials.
Delicious Tofu Bimibop and rice was so tasty. Servers were so friendly. Totally recommend for dinner in your way to the United Centre.
We had an awesome  at this place. We liked the great environment and the meals. The staff are super attentive. I am content we finally managed to try this restaurant.
The food was absolutely amazing. The owner is Korean and knows authentic food. All three flavors were amazing! Great food out with friends. We all enjoyed ourselves!
The Pork bowl was delicious
From Denver— in town to visit a friend. This place has killer service and amazing food for a super great price. Staff: 10/10 Food: 10/10

First off, this place has AMAZING customer service! I was in town for a concert and was wanting to find a place to eat after. I had contacted this establishment, along with others, asking if it would be possible for them to keep their doors open longer so that people could come eat after the concert. The gentleman running it not only responded really quickly, but was awesome enough to stay open so we would be able to eat! He, and the two ladies that worked, were very nice with smiles all around! The food was delicious! I had the pork belly and spicy wings, and we also had bulgolgi, brisket, and soup around the table. Everything was good! Very decent priced as well! I will def be back next time I have some time in Chicago!

So the picture doesn’t look super appetizing, but the taste made up for it! The brisket had really good flavor with light salt and pepper. I wasn’t a huge fan of the kimchis, think the seasoning was a little off or they weren’t quite ripe. There’s a huge mound of rice beneath the brisket - which I love - and had a lot of leftovers!
My wife and I stopped in a Sunday night and experienced the best Bulgogi and Kalbi I've had in Chicago. Really high quality meats. Will be back to try more.

This place is amazing! If you like BBQ you must try the ribs, better then the last six places I've been. If you like heat, I'd highly recommend the spicey rice cake skewers, simply amazing. I travel some and though I try new places, often they are the same thing in a slighty different package. Here however, a  friendly and open atmosphere accompanies amazing BBQ. I'll definitely be stopping by evertime I'm in town. Great job!
Delicious food and great customer service.
Food is delicious.
Really loved the rice cake skewers, ribs, and pork belly. Would definitely go back. Food was delicious, portion sizes were good.

This is one of the best places to order take out, if you are two people you can get a combo 3 meats 3 sides for like 35 bucks and it's a ton of amazing food!!! Seriously everything melts in your mouth and it's really tasty and high quality ingredients.  Try it!
Love the food
Great food and wonderful service.

This place felt like a scam.  I ordered "Jumbo" korean chicken wings and this is what i got.  1. they are not jumbo 2. they are not even all wings.  They look like Tysons anytizers and tasted average at best.
Food was awesome and the staff was SUPER friendly!  I got the ribs and kimchi fries and loved them both. Also, it’s a small, independent business, so I’m glad to support!

It's unfortunate but we didn't think this was great.  The food seemed overpriced and the meat was greasy.  We had the brisket and pork belly (the better of the two) which were both well seasoned but not worth revisiting.  Perhaps the beef rib is much better but I'm not sure we'll find out.

The service was not at all what I expected! I tried this place out a few times due to the fact my wife loves Korean food! There is always the same rude man working who makes us both very uncomfortable! I highly would recommend going to any other restaurant but here if your looking for good customer service!
This place and its staff are amazing. Stopped in to escape a thunderstorm and couldn't have been more surprised by the great korean bbq and excellent staff
This place simply knows how to please their clients. Constantly with a friendly demeanor. The food is affordably priced, regularly tasty and clean.
Amazing for the price, sides were fresh and meat cooked perfectly. Loved the Pork Belly and Kimchi.  Friendly and casual environment. Would absolutely come here again.
Finally a place that serves authentic Korean BBQ'd dog.
Excellent food and really helpful and nice staff. Casual place but the food was super high quality and delicious. Lots of vegetarian options too!
What a find.  Love this place.  Food is fantastic.  The Kalbi ribs win the day.  Meat falls right off the bone.  Beef rice bowl was fresh..... and the egg on top.... yummo.
Nice place, friendly staff and very good food. The portions are a decent size.
Pleasant experience, the owner is super nice and so was his staff. Has only been open for less than a year so I can’t wait to see the success of this gem!

This food was pretty good. I decided to come to this place because I watch a lot of Korean vloggers on YouTube so I've been wanting to try a Korean restaurant that wasn't a cook it your self KBBQ. We were going to a Blackhawks game and it was pretty close  We ordered the green onion pancake which was too soft and kind of bland.. I prefer a more crispy pancake but it came with a spice to dip in for more flavor. We also ordered their jumbo wings that are not jumbo anymore (half spicy half savory) an order of 8 wings for $10.. they were pretty small. We also ordered the SoJu Ribs and Grilled Pork Belly. It came with rice and I got kimchi with it that was okay. The Pork needs more flavor but they have us a spice to dip/pour on it. We also got an order of Army Soup. It was spicy and pretty good. We got it with ramen rice cakes and pork belly. I've been to Korea and I remember their meat being so full of flavors which is why I'm giving this a 3 star review. I'd give them 3.5 if I could but it's not an option.  The service was great though! Our waiter was so nice and very helpful.
Small but delicious portions. Reasonably priced and good service
Food is great! Always find myself craving it. Quick service and friendly staff. Kimchi is homemade and amazing!
The food was good

I’ve been here multiple times already with my girlfriend and I must say I’ve been pleasantly surprised. While I was skeptical of what “modern kbbq” would be like at first, I’ve seen this place evolve into a great fast casual option for kbbq without the hassle. I did miss the myriad of side dishes that traditional kbbq offered. However, it actually did save some time on service and really liked the fact that I could just order a single serving of kbbq instead of being forced to order 2 portion minimums. In terms of the food, every meat is seasoned well and cooked for you. I’ve REALLY enjoyed the kalbi (very unique cooking method and presentation) and ribeye the most and pork belly had various spices that kept things interesting. I think the prices are reasonable for the portions considering what other places are charging these days... I’m excited to see what else they’ll add to the menu in the future!

Came back here to try the wings and ribeye, definitely not a fan. Sauces were plain and on the side for some reason. Unseasoned, oily, undercooked chicken wings and too expensive. Feels like I got robbed.
This place is pretty darn good

Outstanding! The ribs were tremendous as were the sides and rice. Really good value as well. I was the only customer when I was in there, which is a shame. More people need to get on this! Super convenient if you're going to the United Center. I will definitely come here again.
The food is perfection the Manager/ Owner listens to there customers and tries there absolute best to give the consumers a great tasteful experience. Chicago Best!

Great place for high-quality restaurant Korean BBQ at fast-casual prices. Many dishes were under $10 and the bigger BBQ platters around $12. They’re served as sets, with sides included, so are great also for anyone alone to have a variety of dishes in one order.

Hidden gem of a place. High quality of meat cooked korean style. Side dishes are done in a mix of modern and traditional fashion. If you are a fan of korean food or looking to try something new, this is the place.
Yummy food. Good for one on one conversations.

This place is unique in it's kind for a few reasons - fast casual KBBQ where the cooking is done for you; this place supports local produce and farmers; the quality of products for the price is outstanding; you get to personalize/individual your order to your needs on a lot of items, like picking your 2 veggie sides or being able to choose what you want in your soup. I love the army soup - one of the best I've ever had. Meat will speak for itself in quality and the seasoning is spot-on. The space is small but the service is extremely friendly and tried to accommodate everyone.

Came here during the Laver Cup tournament at the United Center — late Sept Fri, at 5p. Seems the staff was grossly unprepared for the influx of customers coming between matches. We waited ONE FULL HOUR  and our food still had not arrived. Also noticing that they were serving food out of sequence of the orders placed. We finally gave up and asked for a refund. They did not seem to have a system at all for basic tracking of which table ordered what. Solution can be as simple as putting order numbers, giving these to each table, and then preparing and serving in that sequence. It’s not rocket science!! Also may help to staff up when there are events at the United Center. People come here expecting a “quick casual” experience. We were not expecting Fast Food. But it quickly turned into Very Slow Food, and then ultimately — No Food!!  Worst. Restaurant. Experience. Ever.
Worst Korean food ever... Salty, soggy and burned. Really not recommend.

I stopped by this place and had a great meal! I ordered the dino sized Kalbi ribs which came out perfectly cooked. The flavorful meat comes balanced with a side of rice and your choice of veggies. I went with the kimchi and sliced cucumbers, which added some nice crunch to the meal.  I saw that they also do delivery via Grubhub, Uber Eats, Caviar etc. so I'd recommend that if you can't make it to the restaurant. Looking forward to coming here again with friends to try out some of the other dishes!

Loved the food. Army soup is a great starter to split. The Kalbi Ribs are so tender with a great crust, and the Gochujang Chicken had great flavor. Interested to see how the staff will handle bigger crowds/more parties to accommodate. Would recommend and will come back.
Food is amazing. They're trying to mix fast casual with sit down service and that part is mostly confusing. But the awesomeness of the food mostly makes up for it.
Amazing.
Food was terrific and fresh.  Staff was friendly.  BYOB!  Definitively would go back.

Things are coming up Milhouse for the Near West Side now that we finally have Korean BBQ in the area. I was hoping for an original take on Korean BBQ and was not disappointed. The dinosaur like size of the kalbi short ribs allows the chef to get a solid char on the outside while keeping the savory sweetness of the BBQ on the inside. The menu is all BBQ items and BYOSoju as of this writing. Definitely check this place out!
Brand new Korean spot on Ashland focusing on BBQ. All items come in a bento box with meat, rice, and pickled vegetables. Food was good, the pickled cucumbers were tasty. Bulgogi was solid as well.
